-- Results for S&P 500 companies seen up 5 percent
-- 
-- Mon Apr 9, 2007 5:56am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/09/us-usa-results-survey-idUSN0930363620070409

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - First-quarter earnings for S&P 500 companies are expected to rise 5.0 percent, compared with 5.1 percent forecast last week and 9.2 percent forecast when the quarter began, according to a survey by Reuters Estimates. 

 Pre-announcement activity for all publicly traded U.S. companies has been negative for April month to date, according to the survey. These companies have reported 13 positive forward-looking guidance statements and 38 negative outlooks, yielding a positive-to-negative pre-announcement ratio of 0.34, the survey found. Through April 9, 29 S&P 500 companies have reported their quarterly earnings. Of these companies, 62.07 percent beat estimates, 20.69 percent missed estimates and 17.24 percent matched estimates, Reuters Estimates said.